    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>white long grain rice </strong>to a pot with a lid with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and 175ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[230ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span><strong> cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/basa-katsu-with-amai-sauce-and-apple-slaw/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, add a handful of <strong>flour</strong> to a plate</p><p>Crack your<strong> egg[s]</strong> into a shallow bowl and beat with a fork</p><p>Add your<strong> panko breadcrumbs</strong> to another plate</p><p>Coat your <strong>basa fillet[s]</strong> in the <strong>flour</strong>, tap off the excess, then add into the <strong>beaten egg</strong> and finally press into the <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> firmly to evenly coat all over</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/basa-katsu-with-amai-sauce-and-apple-slaw/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a pot over a low heat</p><p>Add your <strong>tomato ketchup</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until thick and sticky, then remove from the heat and set aside for serving \u2013 this is your <strong>amai sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/basa-katsu-with-amai-sauce-and-apple-slaw/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely grate your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Top, tail, peel and grate your<strong> carrot[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/basa-katsu-with-amai-sauce-and-apple-slaw/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut your <strong>apple[s]</strong> (skin on) into matchsticks and discard the core[s]</p><p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong> finely</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/basa-katsu-with-amai-sauce-and-apple-slaw/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> (enough to coat the base of the pan) over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>breaded</strong> <strong>basa</strong> (cooking for 4 or more? Do this in batches!) and cook for 4-5 min on each side, pressing down firmly with a spatula until the outside is golden and the fish is cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>basa katsu</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/basa-katsu-with-amai-sauce-and-apple-slaw/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine the<strong> grated ginger</strong>, <strong>grated carrot</strong>, <strong>apple matchsticks</strong>, <strong>sliced spring onion</strong> and your <strong>mayo</strong> in a large bowl \u2013 this is your<strong> zingy apple slaw</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/basa-katsu-with-amai-sauce-and-apple-slaw/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>basa katsu </strong>into strips</p><p>Serve the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>basa katsu</strong> with the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>rice </strong>and <strong>zingy apple slaw </strong>to the side</p><p>Drizzle over the <strong>amai sauce</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
